The paper discusses machine learning techniques for resource efficiency and robustness, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on techniques for reducing model size and computational complexity in deep neural networks. The second likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper mentions the vision of the Internet-of-Things and autonomous navigation as driving factors for resource-efficient machine learning. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper discusses probabilistic graphical models for treating uncertainty in machine learning systems. The fourth likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper mentions the importance of maintaining and providing uncertainty estimates in real-world systems. The fifth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper focuses on techniques for reducing precision in neural networks to improve resource efficiency.
